==English==
===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1786|1786]], from French [[carafe]], from Italian [[caraffa]], probably from Arabic {{ARchar|[[غرفة]]}} (''ghúrfa'' [[cup]] or [[dipper]]), from {{ARchar|[[غرف]]}} (''ghárafa'', to [[ladle]]).

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kəˈɹæf/}}

===Noun===
'''carafe''' (''plural:'' '''carafes''')

#A [[bottle]], usually [[glass]] and with a [[flared]] [[lip]], used for serving [[water]], [[wine]], or other [[beverage]]s.
#A glass [[pot]] with a [[spout]] for pouring, used for both serving [[coffee]] and as a [[receptacle]] during the [[brewing]] process.

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Arabic: {{ARchar|[[غرافة]]}} (gharrá:fa) {{f}}
*French: carafe {{f}}, [[carafon]] {{m}}
*German: [[Karaffe]] {{f}}, [[Wasserflasche]] {{f}}
{{mid}}
*Spanish: [[garrafa]] {{f}}
{{bottom}}

